  "local_port": 43540,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is smart strategy to prepare for CMAT 2017?",
  "response": "Preparing for the CMAT (Common Management Admission Test) requires a strategic approach to ensure you cover all topics effectively and manage your time efficiently. Here are some smart strategies to prepare for CMAT 2017:\n\n1. **Understand the Exam Pattern and Syllabus**:\n   - Familiarize yourself with the CMAT exam pattern, including the types of questions, marking scheme, and time allotted.\n   - The CMAT generally includes sections such as Quantitative Techniques & Data Interpretation, Logical Reasoning, Language Comprehension, and General Awareness. Ensure you know the topics covered under each section.\n\n2. **Create a Study Plan**:\n   - Develop a realistic and structured study schedule that allows you to dedicate time to each section regularly.\n   - Prioritize sections or topics you find challenging and allocate more time to practice them.\n\n3. **Strengthen Your Basics**:\n   - Focus on building a strong foundation in quantitative topics by revising basic mathematics concepts.\n   - Improve your grasp of grammar, vocabulary, and reading comprehension for the Language Comprehension section.\n\n4. **Practice Logical Reasoning**:\n   - Logical reasoning requires practice and familiarity with different types of puzzles and question patterns. Invest time in solving various reasoning questions daily.\n\n5. **Stay Updated on General Awareness**:\n   - Read newspapers, magazines, and online portals to stay informed about current affairs, business news, and general knowledge topics.\n   - Consider creating notes or flashcards on important events, personalities, and terminology.\n\n6. **Use Quality Study Material**:\n   - Invest in reputable CMAT preparation books and online resources. Some popular publishers and authors include Arun Sharma for Quant and Word Power Made Easy by Norman Lewis for vocabulary.\n\n7. **Practice Mock Tests**:\n   - Regularly take full-length mock tests to simulate the exam environment and improve your time management skills.\n   - Analyze your performance in mock tests to identify areas of improvement and adjust your study plan accordingly.\n\n8. **Review and Revise**:\n   - Regular revision is essential to retain concepts and formulas. Schedule weekly or bi-weekly revision sessions.\n   - Keep a summary sheet or notes for quick revisions during the last few weeks before the exam.\n\n9. **Focus on Time Management**:\n   - Learn to manage your time effectively during the exam by practicing questions within a set time limit.\n   - Develop strategies to tackle difficult questions efficiently or decide when to move on to maximize your score.\n\n10. **Stay Positive and Healthy**:\n    - Maintain a balanced lifestyle with sufficient rest, exercise, and a healthy diet to keep your mind sharp and focused.\n    - Staying positive and confident is crucial to dealing with stress during preparation and on exam day.\n\nBy following these strategies, you can enhance your preparation and improve your chance of achieving a high score on the CMAT 2017.",
